AMQP

@ Exchange binds publisher to a queue.
@ Common exchange types are fanout, direct exchange and topic
@ Fanout - all messages go to all subcribing queue
@ Direct exchange - publisher has a routing key and queue has a binding key . Message gets delivered to the queue
when the routing key matches the binding key
@ Topic - * and #, * can have only one word, # can hold one or more types.
@ Stop the RabbitMQ - rabbitmqctl stop
@ Start it in detached mode - rabbitmq-server -detached
